The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Tamluk, Aug. 28: Nandigram and Khejuri celebrated Rakhi, but with a difference. 

 Bhoomi Uchchhed Pratirodh Committee and CPM activists tied the bands on supporters who were forced to flee home because of the violence. 

 Calcutta: The government will help ITC get 3 acres on lease from the port trust. The company wants a plot behind its Kidderpore tobacco plant for its expansion. The chief secretary and the industries secretary met on Tuesday to discuss the plan.

 Calcutta: Most of the land for Bhusan, Balaji and Abhijeet Group steel plants will be bought directly from owners, the government said. The companies want around 9,600 acres in Purulia and Burdwan.




